A bunch of small fixes to get warm starting working properly, mostly arising
from the addition of resolve_node in update_tree_bound. It's doubtful the use
of this function is really a good idea anyway, but good to have it working to
do some comparison. There's also some funniness around the saving of solutions
from one solve to the next that still needs to be cleaned up. I mostly got rid
of the use of the warm_start->ub, warm_start->best_sol, etc. in favor of just
using env->ub, env->best_sol, etc. It's not clear that it even makes sense to
save solutions in a solution pool, since all previously generated solutions
are stored in the tree and get checked explicitly anyway when updating the
tree bound. There's still a lot to clean up...

(cherry picked from commit de9e3c90be4a219ab4acd61019cb0e0e26d3fd2e)
